Hi Sylvain,
I did some imaging of beads with our Light-sheets (MuVi Luxendo and Lavision UMII)and to be honest, I don`t see your PSFs so bad; looking at the PSF from some confocal, I remember seeing patterns similar to what you show here;  I suppose that a critical info is where was the beam waist (if Gaussian..) and the center of the det lens in relation to the beads; I generally see many aberrations when imaging on the outer part of detection lens (as expected) or with not well aligned sheets; I can send you some snapshots of beads image in ECi where PSF quality is very different in the FOV;
One test would be to see the distortion is coming from the detection or the illumination; maybe trying different sheet alignments, detection lens, ROI in the FOV? Hope it help and just let me know if you need more info; cheers, Alessandro

